**Goal**
- Centralize **toasts/notifications** so UX is consistent and we avoid duplicate implementations.


**Rules**
- Provide a single shared notification system (e.g., `<ToastProvider/>`, `useToast()`), exported from `packages/ui` or `src/components/ui`.
- Do **not** create local/feature-specific toast implementations.
- Support variants (success/error/info/warn) via theme tokens.
- Respect motion/accessibility preferences (reduced motion, announce live regions).


**Checklist (Definition of Done)**
- [ ] All new notifications use the shared `useToast()` or `<Toast />` API.
- [ ] No duplicated toast libraries or one-off components in features.
- [ ] Visuals follow the central theme (tokens only).


**Example structure**
- `packages/ui/src/notification/*` or `frontend/src/components/ui/notification/*`
- `useToast.ts`, `<ToastViewport/>`, `<Toast/>`, `<Toaster/>` exported and documented.